                            <comment id="40603" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 23 Oct 2008 04:00:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Spring itself also proxies EntityManager references, but it does proxy all exposed extension interfaces as well... Seems that Seam is not going that far.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OK, we&apos;ll be revising that cast then: probably first checking for a direct implementation of the HibernateEntityManager interface (which is preferable since even extended functionality may be decorated); if that&apos;s not possible, then check the delegate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="40604" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 23 Oct 2008 04:16:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okidoki, this should be fixed in tonight&apos;s upcoming 2.5.6 snapshot (&lt;a href=&quot;http://static.springframework.org/downloads/nightly/snapshot-download.php?project=SPR&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://static.springframework.org/downloads/nightly/snapshot-download.php?project=SPR&lt;/a&gt;). Feel free to give it a try...&lt;/p&gt;

